description: Seven passengers were injured when United Airlines Flight 85 from Tel Aviv to Newark, New Jersey experienced several minutes of severe turbulence due to a sudden change in wind direction. The flight was diverted to Stewart International Airport, 70 miles north of New York City. NBC News’ George Solis reports.
title: Passengers injured when United Airlines flight experiences severe turbulence

description: Kim Mulkey, the legendary Louisiana State University women's basketball coach, said twice Saturday she hadn't yet read The Washington Post's profile on her everlasting athletic career.
title: LSU coach Kim Mulkey responds to questions about Washington Post profile, saying she hasn’t read it

description: The livelihoods of thousands of workers who process goods passing through the Port of Baltimore hang in the balance as cargo shipments grind to a halt after a container ship crashed into the Francis Scott Key Bridge this week.
title: Port of Baltimore workers were bracing for a busy summer season. Now thousands face an uncertain future.

description: AT&T is investigating a leak earlier this month that dumped millions of customers' data, including personal information such as social security numbers, on the dark web.
title: AT&T investigating leak that dumped millions of customers’ data on dark web

description: A three-ship convoy left a port in Cyprus on Saturday with 400 tons of food and other supplies for Gaza as concerns about hunger in the territory soar.
title: Ships with a second round of aid for Gaza have departed Cyprus as concerns about hunger soar

description: A three-ship convoy left a port in Cyprus on Saturday with 400 tons of food and other supplies for Gaza as concerns about hunger in the territory soar.
title: Ships with a second round of aid for Gaza have departed Cyprus as concerns about hunger soar

description: Lizzo announced Friday that she is quitting the music business because she is "tired of putting up with being dragged by everyone in my life and on the internet.”
title: Lizzo says she's tired of being 'dragged by everyone' on the internet: 'I QUIT'

description: A Missouri teenager who was brutally beaten in what officials called a "deranged display of violence" by another teen is out of the intensive care unit but has limited speech and trouble walking on her own, an attorney for the family said.
title: Missouri teen beaten in viral video is out of ICU but has limited speech and trouble walking on her own, attorney says

description: Trump says many Americans are living in the country "probably as hostages." U.S. officials say they're trying to free two U.S. citizens currently jailed there.
title: Trump exaggerates claim that many Americans are 'hostages' in Afghanistan

description: The U.S. continues to fund and expand highways, even as some parts of the world invest in greener infrastructure over concerns about global warming and amid a broader movement away from cars.
title: As some countries spurn cars, the U.S. continues to embrace highways

description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy dismissed a longtime aide and several advisers on Saturday in a continuing reshuffle while Russia unleashed fresh attacks overnight.
title: Zelenskyy fires more aides in a reshuffle as Russia launches drones and missiles across Ukraine

description: The Merrie Monarch Festival, a weeklong cultural event in Hilo, Hawaii features the best hālau hula, or hula schools, from across the country.
title: Hawaii’s biggest hula festival is honoring Lahaina wildfire victims this year

description: The family of Elaysha Gilliam, a pregnant mother of four found dead in Kansas City, Missouri, wants to know why the police investigation has stalled.
title: A family is searching for answers after a pregnant mother was found dead in a Kansas City park

description: After racking up thousands of dollars in debt, some borrowers are deleting the apps from their phones to avoid getting prodded to spend more.
title: ‘I am so scared of them now’: Burned from overspending, some ‘buy now, pay later’ users warn others away

description: A new national security law has deepened fears about self-censorship in the arts in Hong Kong, one of the world’s biggest art markets.
title: Art world descends on Hong Kong as security laws spur censorship fears

description: Heavily armed police cordoned off part of a Dutch town on Saturday, saying that multiple people were being held hostage, and have evacuated nearby homes.
title: Police say multiple people are being held hostage in a Dutch town. They have evacuated nearby homes

description: After NBC News reported on a new transplant technique for lung cancer, a California man with advanced cancer reached out to Northwestern Medicine and received a double lung and liver transplant.
title: A doctor with lung cancer got a lifesaving treatment after seeing an NBC News report

description: The United States has welcomed the formation of a new Palestinian autonomy government, signaling it is accepting the revised Cabinet lineup as a step toward Palestinian political reform.
title: The U.S. welcomes the new Palestinian government following its repeated calls for political reform

description: Radio Free Asia is withdrawing from Hong Kong, the U.S.-funded media outlet said, citing rising concerns about press freedom in the Chinese territory.
title: Radio Free Asia closes Hong Kong bureau, citing security law concerns

description: Former President Donald Trump shared a video on social media Friday that included an image of President Joe Biden bound and restrained in the back of a pickup truck.
title: Trump shares video with image depicting Biden tied up in the back of a pickup truck

description: Seven people were hurt, none seriously, after a United Airlines plane headed to a New York City-area airport experienced high winds and turbulence, officials said.
title: 7 hurt after Newark-bound United flight experiences turbulence

description: DJ Horne scored 19 points and North Carolina State kept its magical NCAA Tournament run alive, beating Marquette 67-58 on Friday night to reach the Elite Eight for the first time since 1986.
title: N.C. State upsets Marquette in the Sweet 16 to keep March Madness run alive

description: A California man convicted in the death of his mother was the subject of an "intense manhunt" and arrested in Mexico after walking away from a transitional facility without notice, authorities said this week.
title: California man convicted in mother's death arrested for probation violation in Mexican beach town

description: The family of a severely diabetic man whom authorities said died at the hands of a nurse overseeing his care last year has filed a wrongful death suit against the facility where he lived, alleging it allowed the nurse to berate and bully him, and ultimately cause his death.
title: Nurse charged in the deaths of 17 patients berated and bullied diabetic man before giving lethal insulin dose, suit says

description: The cause of the Dali cargo ship's crash into the Key Bridge in Baltimore is not yet known, but it has focused attention on the problem of contaminated fuel.
title: Baltimore bridge crash brings scrutiny to contaminated fuel, an 'open secret' in shipping

description: An endangered fish found off the coast of Florida is exhibiting strange behavior, including "spinning and whirling." The government is mounting an emergency response.
title: 'Spinning and whirling': Strange fish behavior sparks emergency government response

description: The heartbroken mother of a Mississippi teen who died after he was run over by a police cruiser last week is mourning the milestones she'll never get to see her only son achieve.
title: Family of Mississippi teen who died after being run over by police search for answers and accountability

description: A Texas appeals court has upheld a lower court’s injunction blocking the state from investigating parents who provide their trans children with gender-affirming medical treatments, which Gov. Greg Abbott has called abusive.
title: Texas appeals court blocks state from probing transgender kids' parents
